      "note_no": "3556",
      "note": "Allah's Creation was pure and good in itself. All the mischief or corruption was introduced by Evil, viz., arrogance, selfishness, etc. See n. 3541 to 30:30 above. As soon as the mischief has come in, Allah's mercy and goodness step in to stop it. The consequences of Evil must be evil, and this should be shown in such partial punishment as \"the hands of men have earned,\" so that it may be a warning for the future and an invitation to enter the door of repentance (see also n. 5360)."
